Author: dwygaming#0000
Content:
Attention to voters for election 2018 that voted for me : As you may know, We were lucky, and we mined a large block very early.
I announced that I'd send rewards every 4 monthes, but the fact that this huge block "happened" made me reconsider my prediction : I was too stressed keeping funds that are not mine, and I decided to send the first part yesterday.
All voters (who voted for me ^^) should have received their part of the 30% mining, as promised. Thanks again for your support. Feel free to contact me if you want the tx details.
For information, I based the amount on yesterday's "Reward by Miner" from http://www.notarystats.info and made calculation with : 11639.42.
Next one will be in 4 monthes approx from now, but could be sooner if luck happens again.

Author: gcharang#0000
Content: Hi all! We now have all of our developer documentation available at https://komodo-platform.readthedocs.io/en/latest/ . The current github wikis at https://github.com/KomodoPlatform/komodo/wiki, https://github.com/KomodoPlatform/KomodoPlatform/wiki and https://github.com/KomodoPlatform/Agama/wiki, https://github.com/KomodoPlatform/BarterDEX/wiki will continue to get updated and their updates incorporated into the readthedocs version. You are all welcome to visit https://komodo-platform.readthedocs.io/en/latest and go through the docs. If you find any formatting errors, typos or mistakes please inform me. I will make sure that both the github version and the readthedocs version get updated. Also welcome are suggestions about the titles of pages relative order of things inside the docs etc., If you feel like contributing to our documentation to create developer journeys or clearer explanations of things or docs explaining how some of the stuff fits together(Ex: starting from a user acquiring their first KMD -> safely manage it using agama -> use jumblr to anonymize their funds -> use barterDEX to buy other coins(This could be the first step when acquiring KMD)  ), you can fork the repo https://github.com/gcharang/KomodoPlatformdocs and submit PRs. If you have never used git, fear not! it's not really hard (I used it for the first time last month and am already half-decent at it üôÇ ).  Try: https://www.nearform.com/blog/first-time-with-open-source/ , to create readme files: https://guides.github.com/features/mastering-markdown/ git commands: https://git-scm.com/docs/giteveryday . How to contribute to the docs is available at https://github.com/gcharang/KomodoPlatformdocs/blob/master/README.MD
